This paper is about multilingual natural language processing, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses transfer learning, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of corpora for machine translation and sequence tagging, which are tasks commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the importance of comparing results, which is relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks, which is a common technique in deep learning (cs.DL).
